This paper discusses the development of a toolbox for fuzzy rule interpolation, which is a technique commonly used in fuzzy control systems. The paper also mentions the use of advanced fuzzy inference techniques and GUI tools in future work. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) are also possible sub-categories, as they may involve the use of fuzzy logic and control systems.
